tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine and chloride, suggesting possible mild renal impairment or dehydration. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, raising suspicion for renal dysfunction and possible metabolic derangement. HbA1c is low, which may reflect anemia or recent changes in glucose control. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further renal evaluation and assessment for underlying metabolic or systemic conditions.
